<style>
    .card {
        width: 340px;
        height: 430px;
    }

    .col {
        margin-right: 8px;
    }

    h1 {
        margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    h3 {
        margin-bottom: 30px
    }
</style>

<div class="col flex-wrap text-wrap text-break text-center">
    <h1>Welcome, Manager!</h1>
    <h3>What would you like to do?</h3>

    <div class="container-fluid d-flex">

        <div class="col container-fluid d-flex justify-content-center">
            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Fortnight Records</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">As a manager, you can record your hours worked on specific activities by associating those hours with the respective WBS. By entering the hours worked in each WBS for each day, you ensure an accurate record of time spent on different projects or tasks. You can also navigate between fortnights, if it's a past or future fortnight, no changes are allowed, in the current fortnight, you can edit if necessary.</p>
                    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Records" asp-action="Create" class="btn btn-primary mt-auto">Go to</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col container-fluid d-flex justify-content-center">
            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Reports</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">As the project manager responsible for overseeing the distribution of tasks and the progress of the team's activities, you have access to a report in Power BI that allows you to easily identify the Work Breakdown Structure (WBS), with the highest number of time notes, to make informed decisions about resource allocation and time management.</p>
                    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="" asp-action="" class="btn btn-primary mt-auto">Go to</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

</div>